    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T07:04:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T07:04:00-05:00"
                n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#17)]" subtype="historical-document"
                type="document" xml:id="d710a-17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1845</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName> Notes</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d710a-17fn2">
                        <p>Transcribed for this volume from longhand notes in pencil. In interviews
                            with a Department of State historian on January 25 and February 8, 1960,
                                <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName> expressed certainty
                            (since at earlier conferences of Heads of Government it had been his
                            practice, without exception, to transcribe his notes into minutes or
                            memoranda of conversations) that he transcribed these notes into a
                            memorandum of conversation shortly after the meeting took place. Because
                            of <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName>’s reference to the
                            peace feeler from Japan, it is possible that such a memorandum would
                            have been given special security handling, but a search of the
                            Department’s various file collections and of the <persName
                                corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                                >Byrnes</persName> Papers has failed to bring such a memorandum to
                            light. A literal transcription of the original notes is therefore
                            printed here. For a fuller reconstruction of this <persName
                                corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_SGIV1"
                                >Stalin</persName> conversation, prepared by <persName
                                corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName> in March 1960 on the basis of
                            these notes and from memory, see <ref target="#d1419">document No.
                                1419</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</p>
                        <p>For another account of this meeting, see <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                                >Byrnes</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Speaking Frankly</hi>, p. 205.
                                <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> subsequently (<hi
                                rend="italic">All in One Lifetime</hi>, p. 290) and erroneously
                            ascribed the subject matter of this conversation to the <persName
                                corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_SGIV1"
                                >Stalin</persName> meeting of July 17. See <hi rend="italic"
                                >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_43">p. 43</ref>.</p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Potsdam</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1945-07-18T15:04:00+03:00">July
                        18, 1945, 3:04 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="right">3 <hi rend="smallcaps">p</hi>.</p>
                <p>S:<note n="3" xml:id="d710a-17fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName>.</note> [blank]</p>
                <p>M<note n="4" xml:id="d710a-17fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>.</note> [blank]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Pres</hi>
                    <note n="5" xml:id="d710a-17fn5">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                            >Truman</persName>.</note>—lakes—Black</p>
                <p>S—I must tell you the<del rend="strikethrough">y</del>
                    <del rend="strikethrough">the</del> news—hands Pres note from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SN1">Sato</persName> &amp; message from the Emperor<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d710a-17fn6">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d586">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, document No. 586</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>B<note n="7" xml:id="d710a-17fn7">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>—I remember that H—
                        H—<note n="8" xml:id="d710a-17fn8">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry Hopkins</persName>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>S—worthwhile <del rend="strikethrough">answer</del> to answer—</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Pres</hi> no respect.</p>
                <p>S—not a war—will want lull—might answer as follows no specific—don’t know
                    character—of K<note n="9" xml:id="d710a-17fn9">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KPF1">Konoye</persName>.</note> Mission—can’t—answer=a
                    refusal</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Pres</hi> satisfactory</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>—factual</p>
                <p>B—what [one word illegible] <del rend="strikethrough">ins</del> inspired it—fear
                    of what you will do—</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>—I think they guess</p>
                <p>S—Can see our forces tanks etc</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>—not only to USSR</p>
                <p>S—to US. Eng &amp; [one word illegible]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Pres</hi>—we had indicati[on] from Sweden<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d710a-17fn10">See <ref target="#d1420">document No. 1420</ref>, <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
